A MERCEDES-Benz AMG-GT that costs about R2,8 million met its maker when it crashed into two other cars. The silver AMG-GT crashed into a red Alfa Romeo Giulia Quadrifoglio that costs about R1,4 million and a BMW X5 worth R1,5 million. In the video, the AMG-GT can be seen smashed on the front right side with the axle completely removed due to the crash. The red Alfa can be seen lying on its side suspended by a street pole with the back of the car destroyed. The video was published by RMG News. 